The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Sanmarg editor dead
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Sanmarg editor dead
                              Ram Awatar Gupta                            
	Calcutta, Sept. 25: Ram Awatar Gupta, editor of the Hindi daily Sanmarg, died on September 23 after a brief illness.        
	He was 85 and is survived by wife Savitri Gupta and grandson Vivek Gupta, the managing director of the Hindi daily.        
	Ram Awatar Gupta was born in the 1920s in Rajasthan and moved to Varanasi at a young age.         
	Days before his death, he was seen at work in his office.         
	He had received the Matushri Puraskar and the Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru Award for National Integration.                                                                                                                                                                         
